<orth>襜褕</orth>
                <pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">chān yú</pron>
                <pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">khljam lo</pron>
                <pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">tɕhiɛm ji̯o</pron>
            </form>
            <def>Chān yú 襜褕 refers to the broad kind of shén yí 深衣, which came to use in Western Han times. Originally, it was a kind of unformal dress; since the Eastern Han, it could be used also on formal occassions. [SUN 1991: 243; ill.: SUN 1991: 60-7, 60-8]
</def>
